1
00:01:35,940 --> 00:01:38,289
[Too Young To Love]

2
00:01:38,470 --> 00:01:41,229
[Episode 5]

3
00:02:20,360 --> 00:02:21,820
I'm leaving! I'm leaving!

4
00:02:26,750 --> 00:02:27,680
Look at the time.

5
00:02:29,079 --> 00:02:30,810
And you're just coming out now.

6
00:02:32,360 --> 00:02:33,750
You did your hair!

7
00:02:34,360 --> 00:02:35,630
Pretty handsome.

8
00:02:38,680 --> 00:02:39,210
Let's go.

9
00:02:44,520 --> 00:02:44,920
Get on.

10
00:02:47,750 --> 00:02:48,910
Sit tight and hold on tight.

11
00:02:48,910 --> 00:02:50,310
The road's really bumpy.

12
00:02:59,450 --> 00:02:59,870
[Luo Ningzi, here are
the scholarship application materials]

13
00:02:59,900 --> 00:03:00,330
[for those foreign music conservatories
you asked for.]

14
00:03:00,360 --> 00:03:00,620
[Take a look first.
If you have any questions,]

15
00:03:00,620 --> 00:03:00,890
[feel free to contact me anytime.]

16
00:03:00,890 --> 00:03:02,270
[Okay, thank you.]

17
00:03:14,960 --> 00:03:17,240
The first class is math.

18
00:03:25,630 --> 00:03:26,150
Lan,

19
00:03:26,630 --> 00:03:29,360
why have you been studying
so diligently lately?

20
00:03:29,520 --> 00:03:30,450
You've changed.

21
00:03:31,310 --> 00:03:32,960
It's senior year. I should study hard.

22
00:03:32,960 --> 00:03:35,890
If I don't study hard,
I won't be able to go to college.

23
00:03:36,190 --> 00:03:36,630
Alright, alright.

24
00:03:36,630 --> 00:03:37,360
Everyone!

25
00:03:38,079 --> 00:03:39,880
Stop what you're doing. Listen.

26
00:03:41,079 --> 00:03:43,140
Today is the first day of senior year.

27
00:03:43,360 --> 00:03:45,090
You've persevered for 2 years.

28
00:03:45,470 --> 00:03:46,600
For this final year,

29
00:03:46,960 --> 00:03:49,890
I hope you can
adjust your attitude towards studying

30
00:03:50,120 --> 00:03:52,120
and improve your study efficiency.

31
00:03:52,310 --> 00:03:53,120
Although

32
00:03:53,710 --> 00:03:55,590
life, like a math problem,

33
00:03:56,560 --> 00:03:58,079
shouldn't have only one solution,

34
00:03:58,079 --> 00:03:58,740
for you all,

35
00:03:59,190 --> 00:04:00,400
in the coming year,

36
00:04:01,120 --> 00:04:03,000
the college entrance exam
is your only option.

37
00:04:03,000 --> 00:04:04,000
So I hope you all

38
00:04:04,800 --> 00:04:05,750
can do your best.

39
00:04:06,430 --> 00:04:07,000
Okay?

40
00:04:07,150 --> 00:04:08,150
-Okay.
-Okay.

41
00:04:08,590 --> 00:04:09,990
Come on, open your books.

42
00:04:16,040 --> 00:04:16,720
Guys,

43
00:04:16,920 --> 00:04:19,480
this weekend
is Hailan University's open day.

44
00:04:19,480 --> 00:04:20,310
A one-day experience pass.

45
00:04:20,310 --> 00:04:21,040
Are you going?

46
00:04:21,040 --> 00:04:22,100
Hailan University

47
00:04:22,310 --> 00:04:24,840
has the best music department
in the country.

48
00:04:25,120 --> 00:04:25,720
I'm going.

49
00:04:25,830 --> 00:04:27,430
Hailan University's cello major

50
00:04:27,430 --> 00:04:28,160
is very famous.

51
00:04:28,160 --> 00:04:29,510
I'm going too. I'm going too.

52
00:04:29,510 --> 00:04:30,640
Ning, are you going?

53
00:04:31,190 --> 00:04:32,430
I'll check my schedule after I go back.

54
00:04:32,430 --> 00:04:33,270
If it works,

55
00:04:33,390 --> 00:04:34,320
I'll go with you.

56
00:04:34,480 --> 00:04:34,720
Mm.

57
00:04:35,830 --> 00:04:37,159
What about you, Xiaole?

58
00:04:37,190 --> 00:04:38,520
What about you, Xiaole?

59
00:04:40,630 --> 00:04:42,159
I'm not going.

60
00:04:48,830 --> 00:04:51,830
Didn't someone say he wasn't coming?

61
00:04:56,630 --> 00:04:57,870
The sun was too enthusiastic.

62
00:04:57,870 --> 00:04:59,130
He insisted I come out.

63
00:05:04,070 --> 00:05:04,510
Ning,

64
00:05:04,830 --> 00:05:06,160
recently, my parents and I

65
00:05:06,160 --> 00:05:08,390
have been talking about studying abroad.

66
00:05:08,390 --> 00:05:09,250
I want to ask...

67
00:05:10,190 --> 00:05:12,190
if you have any experience to share.

68
00:05:13,270 --> 00:05:14,430
There's a lot of information online.

69
00:05:14,430 --> 00:05:16,070
There are also
specialized agencies offline.

70
00:05:16,070 --> 00:05:17,470
You can go and ask around.

71
00:05:17,830 --> 00:05:19,830
Then recommend one to me.

72
00:05:20,070 --> 00:05:22,400
The one you choose is definitely the best.

73
00:05:22,630 --> 00:05:23,690
This kind of thing—

74
00:05:23,950 --> 00:05:26,270
the best isn't necessarily the right fit.

75
00:05:26,270 --> 00:05:28,200
You'd better look for it yourself.

76
00:05:29,310 --> 00:05:31,040
I'm going to Lan and the others.

77
00:05:36,750 --> 00:05:38,950
So big.

78
00:05:39,270 --> 00:05:41,070
There's even a tennis court.

79
00:05:41,190 --> 00:05:44,159
There must be lots of handsome guys
in the summer.

80
00:05:50,630 --> 00:05:51,760
Where are those two?

81
00:05:55,630 --> 00:05:56,830
What should I do, Xiaole?

82
00:05:56,830 --> 00:05:58,360
She seems to really hate me.

83
00:06:02,270 --> 00:06:04,510
You're so great. Why would she hate you?

84
00:06:05,270 --> 00:06:07,600
Besides, you sing really well, don't you?

85
00:06:21,060 --> 00:06:25,130
♪ Watching your profile draw near,
I smile like a fool ♪

86
00:06:25,730 --> 00:06:29,400
♪ Every word you said, like a melody,
sprouts in my heart ♪

87
00:06:30,210 --> 00:06:34,230
♪ The sparks between us
burn bright within the notes ♪

88
00:06:34,680 --> 00:06:38,530
♪ How I long for an answer from you ♪

89
00:06:38,860 --> 00:06:40,880
♪ My heart won't stop its racing beat ♪

90
00:06:41,320 --> 00:06:43,730
♪ The sweetness when our eyes meet ♪

91
00:06:42,920 --> 00:06:45,240
These two are pretty cool.

92
00:06:44,220 --> 00:06:47,890
♪ Each time we meet,
it's as if the dream goes on ♪

93
00:06:48,290 --> 00:06:50,480
♪ How I wish to tell you ♪

94
00:06:50,640 --> 00:06:52,860
♪ It's not a coincidence or a miracle ♪

95
00:06:54,930 --> 00:06:57,690
♪ It's destiny ♪

96
00:06:57,900 --> 00:06:59,750
♪ Sharing my earbuds with you ♪

97
00:06:59,770 --> 00:07:01,910
♪ Connecting you to my heartbeat ♪

98
00:07:01,970 --> 00:07:04,020
♪ Scrolling up and down the playlist ♪

99
00:07:04,110 --> 00:07:07,490
♪ Disrupting the rhythm of my breath ♪

100
00:07:07,700 --> 00:07:11,600
♪ On repeat, the song
tells the secret I can't speak ♪

101
00:07:11,710 --> 00:07:13,260
♪ The smile at the corner of your lips ♪

102
00:07:13,630 --> 00:07:16,600
♪ Makes me wonder ♪

103
00:07:16,680 --> 00:07:21,200
♪ If Cupid's golden arrow
has finally found you ♪

104
00:07:25,070 --> 00:07:27,190
Thank you. Thank you.

105
00:07:31,630 --> 00:07:33,240
Not bad, Xiaole.

106
00:07:33,310 --> 00:07:34,870
When did you get this good?

107
00:07:35,120 --> 00:07:36,000
Pretty cool.

108
00:07:37,310 --> 00:07:38,909
There's a lot you don't know.

109
00:07:40,600 --> 00:07:41,720
You sang really well.

110
00:07:41,720 --> 00:07:43,380
What do you think, Luo Ningzi?

111
00:07:48,190 --> 00:07:49,590
It indeed was quite good.

112
00:07:52,190 --> 00:07:53,480
I want to go to the library.

113
00:07:53,480 --> 00:07:54,740
Let's split up for now.

114
00:08:04,430 --> 00:08:05,870
It indeed was quite good.

115
00:08:07,720 --> 00:08:09,190
Let's start from this section.

116
00:08:07,820 --> 00:08:11,050
[Teacher's Music Room 2]

117
00:08:11,830 --> 00:08:13,560
Hand position, hand position.

118
00:08:13,950 --> 00:08:15,210
Move your hand up a bit.

119
00:08:16,750 --> 00:08:18,270
Yes, don't press too hard.

120
00:08:18,270 --> 00:08:18,800
Come.

121
00:08:18,800 --> 00:08:19,860
Give it some space.

122
00:08:36,289 --> 00:08:37,309
[Hailan University Journal]

123
00:08:38,909 --> 00:08:41,270
Ye Mei, Associate Professor of Cello,

124
00:08:41,600 --> 00:08:42,860
Doctoral Supervisor.

125
00:08:46,410 --> 00:08:47,930
[Verdant Campus]

126
00:08:47,950 --> 00:08:50,590
[Ye Mei: The moment you pick up the cello,
you must be devout.]

127
00:08:49,990 --> 00:08:52,450
Professor Ye is a big name
in the cello world.

128
00:08:52,910 --> 00:08:54,170
She's really amazing.

129
00:08:54,270 --> 00:08:56,600
She's trained so many champion students.

130
00:08:59,000 --> 00:08:59,390
Down.

131
00:08:59,360 --> 00:09:01,930
♪ She left in spring ♪

132
00:09:02,920 --> 00:09:05,800
♪ Gone with her was cherry blossoms ♪

133
00:09:06,480 --> 00:09:08,930
♪ On the once youthful face ♪

134
00:09:10,120 --> 00:09:12,800
♪ There were tears amidst confusion ♪

135
00:09:10,390 --> 00:09:12,790
This university even has a tea plantation.

136
00:09:13,680 --> 00:09:15,950
♪ She left in spring ♪

137
00:09:17,020 --> 00:09:19,630
♪ All was like a dream ♪

138
00:09:19,000 --> 00:09:19,400
Yi Lan!

139
00:09:19,460 --> 00:09:23,910
[Recording]

140
00:09:20,400 --> 00:09:23,170
♪ Youth never lasts ♪

141
00:09:24,580 --> 00:09:27,110
♪ Just let her go ♪

142
00:09:28,270 --> 00:09:29,120
Two turtles.

143
00:09:28,280 --> 00:09:30,470
♪ The paper plane that was once set free ♪

144
00:09:30,630 --> 00:09:34,030
♪ Will find its way back
to the old desk and chair at school ♪

145
00:09:34,240 --> 00:09:37,300
♪ All stories have yet to end ♪

146
00:09:37,700 --> 00:09:39,070
♪ Let me write for you ♪

147
00:09:39,130 --> 00:09:42,860
♪ An old CD will witness
our ever-ending dreams ♪

148
00:09:43,000 --> 00:09:43,870
I envy them so much.

149
00:09:43,070 --> 00:09:46,120
♪ Youth is nothing but a farce ♪

150
00:09:46,210 --> 00:09:49,400
♪ In which everyone has fun till the end ♪

151
00:09:49,430 --> 00:09:52,830
♪ It's a pity time always sneaks away ♪

152
00:09:49,630 --> 00:09:50,430
I've decided.

153
00:09:51,630 --> 00:09:53,750
I'm going to apply for the cello major
at Hailan University.

154
00:09:52,990 --> 00:09:55,420
♪ Leaving behind so many headaches ♪

155
00:09:54,270 --> 00:09:55,460
I want to become Professor Ye's student.

156
00:09:55,460 --> 00:09:57,050
♪ We never had the time to look back on ♪

157
00:09:55,870 --> 00:09:56,200
Okay.

158
00:09:57,260 --> 00:09:59,980
♪ Youth is nothing but a farce ♪

159
00:10:00,240 --> 00:10:03,150
♪ We live it wholeheartedly ♪

160
00:10:03,400 --> 00:10:07,040
♪ Joy and sorrow are woven together ♪

161
00:10:04,150 --> 00:10:04,630
Xiaole.

162
00:10:05,150 --> 00:10:06,390
I have a great idea.

163
00:10:07,270 --> 00:10:09,120
I don't think you have ideas.

164
00:10:07,350 --> 00:10:10,730
♪ Every experience will bring me closer ♪

165
00:10:10,030 --> 00:10:12,030
We should form a band together.

166
00:10:11,010 --> 00:10:13,450
♪ To myself ♪

167
00:10:12,240 --> 00:10:13,630
I've already thought of the band name.

168
00:10:13,630 --> 00:10:14,690
It's called Lefan.

169
00:10:17,870 --> 00:10:19,000
You play the guitar.

170
00:10:19,000 --> 00:10:20,150
And I'll sing songs.

171
00:10:20,270 --> 00:10:22,400
We'll be invincible, I'm telling you.

172
00:10:22,510 --> 00:10:23,440
-Lefan?
-Lefan?

173
00:10:24,240 --> 00:10:24,870
What?

174
00:10:24,870 --> 00:10:25,870
That's so cheesy!

175
00:10:27,240 --> 00:10:28,040
I support you!

176
00:10:28,510 --> 00:10:29,510
I support you too!

177
00:10:33,150 --> 00:10:35,360
Which universities do you guys
plan to apply to?

178
00:10:35,360 --> 00:10:37,000
Should we apply to the same one?

179
00:10:37,000 --> 00:10:38,240
I want to study abroad,

180
00:10:38,240 --> 00:10:39,790
but I'm worried I can't get admitted.

181
00:10:39,790 --> 00:10:40,670
But my dad said

182
00:10:40,790 --> 00:10:42,510
it doesn't matter
even if I can't get admitted. At worst,

183
00:10:42,510 --> 00:10:43,910
I'll just take over the family business.

184
00:10:43,910 --> 00:10:45,030
A rich kid indeed.

185
00:10:45,150 --> 00:10:48,510
If you can't get admitted,
you can only inherit the family business.

186
00:10:48,510 --> 00:10:50,890
Lan, which university
do you want to apply to?

187
00:10:50,890 --> 00:10:52,700
[Pre-filled College Application
Preference Form]

188
00:10:51,390 --> 00:10:52,600
Hailan University.

189
00:10:52,910 --> 00:10:53,870
But I checked.

190
00:10:54,390 --> 00:10:57,600
Hailan University's admission score
was 450 last year.

191
00:10:58,150 --> 00:11:00,550
The cello major only admitted 15 students.

192
00:11:00,670 --> 00:11:01,470
I'm thinking,

193
00:11:01,910 --> 00:11:03,570
even if I pass the school exam,

194
00:11:04,150 --> 00:11:06,270
I'm still under a lot of pressure
because of my academic scores.

195
00:11:06,270 --> 00:11:07,510
You can't think like that.

196
00:11:07,510 --> 00:11:08,510
We're not stupid.

197
00:11:09,270 --> 00:11:10,730
When did I say I was stupid?

198
00:11:12,270 --> 00:11:14,510
You're so talented in art.

199
00:11:14,790 --> 00:11:16,870
For the art exam, people usually
hire tutors for focused guidance.

200
00:11:16,870 --> 00:11:19,330
If you work hard,
you'll definitely make it.

201
00:11:21,270 --> 00:11:24,740
[Pre-filled College Application
Preference Form]

202
00:11:28,910 --> 00:11:29,840
I know who to ask.

203
00:11:32,360 --> 00:11:33,270
I think

204
00:11:33,510 --> 00:11:35,000
if you really want to learn,

205
00:11:35,000 --> 00:11:36,360
I'll introduce you

206
00:11:36,390 --> 00:11:37,790
to a professional tutor.

207
00:11:38,390 --> 00:11:39,120
How about it?

208
00:11:40,390 --> 00:11:41,630
I guess that works.

209
00:11:49,000 --> 00:11:49,360
Shan.

210
00:11:49,790 --> 00:11:50,850
Can I get admitted?

211
00:11:51,240 --> 00:11:53,870
Don't worry about that yet.
Human effort is the decisive factor.

212
00:11:53,870 --> 00:11:55,400
You have to work hard first.

213
00:11:59,510 --> 00:12:00,440
Do you want to...

214
00:12:01,000 --> 00:12:01,750
listen to...

215
00:12:02,150 --> 00:12:03,950
my mentor's, i.e. your mom's...

216
00:12:07,270 --> 00:12:08,670
wonderful performance.

217
00:12:09,360 --> 00:12:09,790
Yes.

218
00:12:11,000 --> 00:12:12,200
Let me see where it is.

219
00:12:15,030 --> 00:12:15,560
This one.

220
00:12:33,600 --> 00:12:35,000
My mom is amazing!

221
00:12:35,120 --> 00:12:37,050
She truly deserves to be my mentor.

222
00:12:37,120 --> 00:12:38,120
So professional.

223
00:12:40,510 --> 00:12:41,630
Why didn't you let me listen earlier?

224
00:12:41,630 --> 00:12:43,090
You didn't ask me earlier.

225
00:12:43,870 --> 00:12:44,800
My bad. I forgot.

226
00:12:47,270 --> 00:12:48,730
Since my mom is so amazing,

227
00:12:49,750 --> 00:12:51,120
I can definitely make it too.

228
00:12:51,120 --> 00:12:51,870
You definitely can.

229
00:12:51,870 --> 00:12:52,630
I believe in you.

230
00:12:52,630 --> 00:12:53,360
You can do it.

231
00:12:59,870 --> 00:13:00,670
You continue to listen.

232
00:13:00,670 --> 00:13:01,480
The books have arrived.

233
00:13:01,480 --> 00:13:02,410
I'll go get them.

234
00:13:02,630 --> 00:13:03,000
Okay.

235
00:13:11,600 --> 00:13:13,630
Stop reading and watch the shop for me.

236
00:13:13,630 --> 00:13:14,240
Got it.

237
00:13:22,750 --> 00:13:23,750
Tong Xiaole.

238
00:13:25,150 --> 00:13:26,750
Can you do something useful?

239
00:13:34,000 --> 00:13:34,750
I deduce

240
00:13:35,510 --> 00:13:36,640
that within 2 hours,

241
00:13:37,390 --> 00:13:39,590
no one will come. So I'll read a bit more.

242
00:13:42,150 --> 00:13:42,870
Ning!

243
00:13:44,510 --> 00:13:45,390
Mengmeng!

244
00:13:48,240 --> 00:13:50,000
Come and listen to my mom's performance.

245
00:13:50,000 --> 00:13:50,360
Come.

246
00:13:50,390 --> 00:13:50,870
Hurry.

247
00:13:50,870 --> 00:13:51,400
Sit. Sit.

248
00:13:51,630 --> 00:13:52,560
Listen. Listen.

249
00:13:54,870 --> 00:13:55,400
Chen Fan.

250
00:13:59,750 --> 00:14:00,360
Beg me.

251
00:14:07,870 --> 00:14:09,470
The first string, 4 fingers.

252
00:14:10,910 --> 00:14:12,570
The second string, 3 fingers.

253
00:14:12,600 --> 00:14:13,600
The third string.

254
00:14:14,270 --> 00:14:15,670
Back to the first string.

255
00:14:17,480 --> 00:14:18,790
Then to the second string.

256
00:14:18,790 --> 00:14:21,360
Your fingering is so nimble.

257
00:14:22,000 --> 00:14:24,060
With more practice, you can do it too.

258
00:14:27,670 --> 00:14:28,750
Let me show you.

259
00:14:29,120 --> 00:14:29,450
Okay.

260
00:15:09,270 --> 00:15:10,600
Professor Ye Mei?

261
00:15:15,150 --> 00:15:15,670
Hello.

262
00:15:16,790 --> 00:15:19,150
I'm Luo Ningzi,
a senior from No. 2 High School.

263
00:15:19,150 --> 00:15:21,240
Could you please comment on my playing?

264
00:15:21,240 --> 00:15:23,170
Your basic skills are quite solid.

265
00:15:24,270 --> 00:15:25,270
It's just that...

266
00:15:25,600 --> 00:15:26,930
it lacks some emotions.

267
00:15:28,390 --> 00:15:30,120
If you want to improve further,

268
00:15:30,150 --> 00:15:32,350
welcome to apply to Hailan University.

269
00:15:33,240 --> 00:15:33,840
Thank you.

270
00:15:34,390 --> 00:15:34,990
Keep it up.

271
00:16:07,270 --> 00:16:07,630
Shan.

272
00:16:07,630 --> 00:16:08,230
The books.

273
00:16:08,240 --> 00:16:09,700
Help me put the books back.

274
00:16:23,270 --> 00:16:24,070
Professor Ye.

275
00:16:26,670 --> 00:16:28,240
My name is Yi Lan.

276
00:16:28,480 --> 00:16:30,080
I'm Luo Ningzi's classmate.

277
00:16:30,630 --> 00:16:32,480
I also really want
to get admitted to Hailan University

278
00:16:32,480 --> 00:16:33,750
and become your student.

279
00:16:33,750 --> 00:16:35,010
I admire you very much.

280
00:16:35,270 --> 00:16:36,630
Show me your left hand.

281
00:16:37,870 --> 00:16:38,470
Left hand.

282
00:16:50,670 --> 00:16:52,070
Do you really like music,

283
00:16:52,360 --> 00:16:54,150
or do you just want to use this hobby

284
00:16:54,150 --> 00:16:55,150
to take the art exam

285
00:16:55,150 --> 00:16:57,550
as a stepping stone
to get into university?

286
00:17:00,720 --> 00:17:02,600
Music isn't a whim or a game.

287
00:17:03,630 --> 00:17:05,630
It requires you to work really hard.

288
00:17:05,960 --> 00:17:06,829
Are you ready?

289
00:17:32,200 --> 00:17:34,060
I'm going to my major class first.

290
00:17:36,400 --> 00:17:36,960
Ning.

291
00:17:37,830 --> 00:17:38,640
Your hand...

292
00:17:41,640 --> 00:17:42,440
It's nothing.

293
00:17:42,880 --> 00:17:43,880
The calluses have been rubbed raw.

294
00:17:43,880 --> 00:17:44,680
I'm used to it.

295
00:17:45,640 --> 00:17:46,100
I'm off.

296
00:17:48,110 --> 00:17:49,110
Ning, wait for me.

297
00:18:09,070 --> 00:18:09,480
Ning.

298
00:18:10,160 --> 00:18:12,220
Your performance just now was great.

299
00:18:15,920 --> 00:18:17,110
She said my playing

300
00:18:17,440 --> 00:18:18,440
lacked emotions.

301
00:18:19,400 --> 00:18:22,600
Professor Ye isn't necessarily right
about everything.

302
00:18:28,920 --> 00:18:30,250
I need to find emotions.

303
00:18:33,920 --> 00:18:35,650
I think it was full of emotions!

304
00:18:41,720 --> 00:18:43,640
Your dad's been busy outside these months.

305
00:18:43,640 --> 00:18:45,100
I've been pretty busy too.

306
00:18:45,110 --> 00:18:46,440
Just take good care of yourself

307
00:18:46,440 --> 00:18:47,770
and practice the cello.

308
00:18:48,400 --> 00:18:49,530
Here, have an apple.

309
00:18:50,880 --> 00:18:51,830
Mom, I...

310
00:18:52,550 --> 00:18:53,880
I know you don't like them,

311
00:18:53,880 --> 00:18:55,740
but they're good for your health.

312
00:18:56,640 --> 00:18:57,370
Thanks, Mom.

313
00:19:03,240 --> 00:19:03,550
Mom,

314
00:19:04,070 --> 00:19:06,200
I went to Hailan University last week.

315
00:19:06,440 --> 00:19:08,400
Their music program is pretty good.

316
00:19:08,400 --> 00:19:11,260
If my study abroad application
doesn't go through,

317
00:19:11,440 --> 00:19:13,170
I'll apply to this university.

318
00:19:14,070 --> 00:19:15,720
No matter how good Hailan University is,

319
00:19:15,720 --> 00:19:18,960
it still can't compare to going abroad
to polish your résumé.

320
00:19:18,960 --> 00:19:20,590
Don't worry about things at home.

321
00:19:20,590 --> 00:19:21,920
Just focus on yourself.

322
00:19:23,790 --> 00:19:24,310
Mm.

323
00:19:24,920 --> 00:19:25,550
Got it.

324
00:19:26,240 --> 00:19:27,700
I'm going to practice now.

325
00:19:38,640 --> 00:19:39,070
Mr. Bu.

326
00:19:39,480 --> 00:19:40,740
I understand all that.

327
00:19:41,240 --> 00:19:41,770
Yes, yes.

328
00:19:43,030 --> 00:19:44,890
We're always too busy out of town.

329
00:19:46,160 --> 00:19:46,880
Don't worry.

330
00:19:46,880 --> 00:19:49,210
We'll definitely communicate properly.

331
00:19:56,550 --> 00:19:58,610
What are you messing around with now?

332
00:19:59,240 --> 00:20:00,570
Photos taken by Xiaole.

333
00:20:07,440 --> 00:20:09,300
Your class teacher contacted me.

334
00:20:09,960 --> 00:20:11,590
He said your grades are very good,

335
00:20:11,590 --> 00:20:13,480
and the school has high hopes for you.

336
00:20:13,480 --> 00:20:16,340
I don't know much
about top universities or majors.

337
00:20:16,550 --> 00:20:17,880
What are your thoughts?

338
00:20:35,640 --> 00:20:37,170
Then just put down Finance.

339
00:20:38,790 --> 00:20:40,920
We never managed your studies before.

340
00:20:41,440 --> 00:20:43,100
But you're in senior year now.

341
00:20:43,440 --> 00:20:46,590
From now on, your mom will stay at home
and take good care of you.

342
00:20:46,590 --> 00:20:48,920
You just focus on preparing for the exams.

343
00:20:55,110 --> 00:20:55,400
I...

344
00:20:55,790 --> 00:20:57,790
These photos taken by Xiaole
are pretty good.

345
00:20:57,790 --> 00:20:58,440
Look, Tong.

346
00:20:58,440 --> 00:20:59,370
Just take a look.

347
00:21:00,640 --> 00:21:01,960
Take a good look.

348
00:21:05,310 --> 00:21:05,680
Mom.

349
00:21:07,350 --> 00:21:07,880
I'm fine.

350
00:21:09,310 --> 00:21:10,640
I can take good care of myself.

351
00:21:10,640 --> 00:21:11,840
I think at this stage,

352
00:21:13,110 --> 00:21:15,440
you two should just focus on making money.

353
00:21:22,720 --> 00:21:25,450
Xiaole, you really don't need me
to stay with you?

354
00:21:26,640 --> 00:21:30,100
Then I'll go on a business trip
with your dad tomorrow morning.

355
00:21:36,110 --> 00:21:36,480
Mom,

356
00:21:36,830 --> 00:21:37,400
I made plans with friends.

357
00:21:37,400 --> 00:21:38,530
I'm going out first.

358
00:21:40,550 --> 00:21:41,480
Come back early.

359
00:21:44,350 --> 00:21:45,590
Communicate properly?

360
00:21:45,590 --> 00:21:47,450
Do you think that kid will listen?

361
00:21:47,830 --> 00:21:50,160
He doesn't even know
how to respect us now.

362
00:21:50,550 --> 00:21:53,720
What's wrong? Shouldn't you
listen to our son's opinion on this?

363
00:21:53,720 --> 00:21:54,920
When filling out high school applications,

364
00:21:54,920 --> 00:21:56,160
you told me to let him do as he pleased.

365
00:21:56,160 --> 00:21:57,360
And he argued with me.

366
00:21:57,480 --> 00:21:59,240
Look at all his bad habits now.

367
00:21:59,400 --> 00:22:00,790
And he has such a bad temper!

368
00:22:00,790 --> 00:22:01,850
You're blaming me?

369
00:22:02,160 --> 00:22:03,560
Was it me who spoiled him?

370
00:22:03,640 --> 00:22:05,680
Neither of us usually has time
to discipline him!

371
00:22:05,680 --> 00:22:07,590
After just a few years of schooling,
he started looking down

372
00:22:07,590 --> 00:22:09,440
on his father for reeking of money, huh?

373
00:22:09,440 --> 00:22:10,830
Look at how listless he is!

374
00:22:10,830 --> 00:22:12,640
What can he possibly do in the future?

375
00:22:12,640 --> 00:22:15,550
Maybe I'll have to use my connections
to find him a job!

376
00:22:15,550 --> 00:22:16,880
Why are you always yelling?

377
00:22:16,880 --> 00:22:18,480
How are we supposed
to communicate like this?

378
00:22:18,480 --> 00:22:20,880
On the matter of filling out applications,
shouldn't you listen to his opinion?

379
00:22:20,880 --> 00:22:22,010
I can't believe you.

380
00:22:22,160 --> 00:22:24,830
You just never say anything nice.

381
00:22:31,480 --> 00:22:33,680
The cello major at Hailan University.

382
00:22:42,550 --> 00:22:43,200
Sister,

383
00:22:43,680 --> 00:22:46,240
if you get into the cello major,

384
00:22:46,830 --> 00:22:49,030
you'll become a musician in the future.

385
00:22:49,880 --> 00:22:51,680
Stop playing and come eat first.

386
00:22:57,440 --> 00:22:59,170
The tuition is a bit expensive,

387
00:22:59,240 --> 00:23:00,700
but I can work summer jobs.

388
00:23:00,790 --> 00:23:03,920
I can also work part-time in university
to earn tuition.

389
00:23:08,880 --> 00:23:10,080
It's not about money.

390
00:23:10,160 --> 00:23:10,960
I don't agree.

391
00:23:12,830 --> 00:23:13,290
Well...

392
00:23:16,350 --> 00:23:17,280
Let's eat first.

393
00:23:28,450 --> 00:23:30,300
[Bad news. My dad
doesn't agree with me learning the cello.]

394
00:23:30,300 --> 00:23:31,630
[Wait for me at the usual place.]

395
00:23:34,740 --> 00:23:39,310
[When the sun goes down,
it's time to drink]

396
00:23:37,300 --> 00:23:39,370
So? The place I found
is pretty good, right?

397
00:23:39,370 --> 00:23:41,070
Tonight was
our first successful performance.

398
00:23:41,070 --> 00:23:43,240
We must have a proper celebration feast.

399
00:23:43,240 --> 00:23:45,300
I'll treat you to barbecue. Let's go.

400
00:23:45,640 --> 00:23:46,880
I'm a bit tired today.

401
00:23:47,070 --> 00:23:48,000
Maybe next time.

402
00:23:48,240 --> 00:23:49,140
Next time, it's my treat.

403
00:23:49,140 --> 00:23:51,950
[When the sun goes down,
it's time to drink]

404
00:23:49,310 --> 00:23:50,370
I'm leaving first.

405
00:23:50,550 --> 00:23:51,070
Bye bye.

406
00:24:19,350 --> 00:24:20,790
You scared me.

407
00:24:26,880 --> 00:24:27,480
Tell me.

408
00:24:29,590 --> 00:24:30,920
Why did you come

409
00:24:31,960 --> 00:24:33,090
to your life mentor?

410
00:24:34,590 --> 00:24:36,400
Just those things about my dad.

411
00:24:37,550 --> 00:24:39,280
He always says the same things.

412
00:24:39,480 --> 00:24:40,160
He said

413
00:24:40,350 --> 00:24:41,640
he'll absolutely never support me

414
00:24:41,640 --> 00:24:43,300
in taking the cello as a major.

415
00:24:44,160 --> 00:24:46,110
He also said there's no future
in learning the cello.

416
00:24:46,110 --> 00:24:48,040
I asked him why, and he always said,

417
00:24:48,160 --> 00:24:50,400
"Eat first. That's enough."

418
00:24:56,480 --> 00:24:57,540
Do you think so too?

419
00:24:57,590 --> 00:24:58,250
Why would I?

420
00:24:59,160 --> 00:24:59,960
Of course not.

421
00:25:04,640 --> 00:25:05,240
But...

422
00:25:06,720 --> 00:25:07,550
have you put in the effort?

423
00:25:07,550 --> 00:25:08,240
Of course.

424
00:25:13,200 --> 00:25:15,160
It's just that
I haven't had professional training.

425
00:25:15,160 --> 00:25:16,890
So it's definitely not enough.

426
00:25:18,110 --> 00:25:19,240
Sometimes I'd think

427
00:25:19,720 --> 00:25:22,030
if I put in 100% effort

428
00:25:22,590 --> 00:25:24,590
and I still don't succeed in the end,

429
00:25:24,920 --> 00:25:27,350
my dad would surely be
very disappointed in me.

430
00:25:27,350 --> 00:25:29,350
I'd also lose confidence in myself.

431
00:25:30,790 --> 00:25:31,440
Fine.

432
00:25:32,680 --> 00:25:33,480
Let me ask you.

433
00:25:33,680 --> 00:25:36,240
You said you want to play the cello.
How badly do you want it?

434
00:25:36,240 --> 00:25:37,310
Even in my dreams.

435
00:25:37,400 --> 00:25:38,400
If it's something you dream about,

436
00:25:38,400 --> 00:25:39,310
just do it.

437
00:25:39,550 --> 00:25:40,240
If you don't get admitted this year,

438
00:25:40,240 --> 00:25:41,200
try again next year.

439
00:25:41,200 --> 00:25:42,640
Since it's something you dream about,

440
00:25:42,640 --> 00:25:44,110
how can you give up so easily?

441
00:25:44,110 --> 00:25:45,790
Something you dream about

442
00:25:46,200 --> 00:25:47,200
is called a dream.

443
00:25:48,440 --> 00:25:49,070
Dreams

444
00:25:49,830 --> 00:25:50,960
are very important.

445
00:26:00,880 --> 00:26:02,140
I can't give up easily.

446
00:26:04,400 --> 00:26:05,590
You're teachable.

447
00:26:08,400 --> 00:26:10,030
Then I need to plan properly

448
00:26:10,240 --> 00:26:11,500
how to convince my dad.

449
00:26:12,880 --> 00:26:13,740
What about you?

450
00:26:14,160 --> 00:26:16,160
Which university do you plan to apply to?

451
00:26:16,160 --> 00:26:17,400
I don't need to take the art exam.

452
00:26:17,400 --> 00:26:18,200
It's still early.

453
00:26:18,200 --> 00:26:19,640
You clearly don't know what to apply to,

454
00:26:19,640 --> 00:26:20,790
yet you're lecturing me.

455
00:26:20,790 --> 00:26:21,790
Stop pretending.

456
00:26:23,350 --> 00:26:24,830
I am maturer than you.

457
00:26:27,880 --> 00:26:28,740
How about this?

458
00:26:28,960 --> 00:26:31,830
You participate
in a photography competition

459
00:26:32,030 --> 00:26:33,890
or create a photography account.

460
00:26:33,960 --> 00:26:35,960
Maybe you'll become an instant hit.

461
00:26:38,310 --> 00:26:39,770
What are you "mm"-ing for?

462
00:26:39,830 --> 00:26:42,430
Why do you always refuse
to admit what you like?

463
00:26:47,590 --> 00:26:48,070
Oh.

464
00:26:49,590 --> 00:26:51,050
What are you "oh"-ing for?

465
00:26:53,880 --> 00:26:54,240
Sit.

466
00:26:54,790 --> 00:26:55,050
Sit.

467
00:27:00,070 --> 00:27:00,870
What's up, Bu?

468
00:27:01,640 --> 00:27:02,880
I know exactly

469
00:27:03,590 --> 00:27:04,650
what your level is.

470
00:27:05,400 --> 00:27:06,160
But...

471
00:27:06,290 --> 00:27:07,930
[Pre-filled College Application
Preference Form]

472
00:27:06,310 --> 00:27:07,880
this blank application form...

473
00:27:07,880 --> 00:27:08,210
What?

474
00:27:08,920 --> 00:27:12,250
Did you get yourself
a recommendation offer behind my back?

475
00:27:14,400 --> 00:27:15,460
I haven't decided.

476
00:27:16,880 --> 00:27:18,610
Is it that you haven't decided,

477
00:27:19,070 --> 00:27:20,880
or do your parents have other opinions?

478
00:27:20,880 --> 00:27:22,400
They're fine with whatever.

479
00:27:22,400 --> 00:27:23,790
I just haven't made up my mind.

480
00:27:23,790 --> 00:27:24,650
How about this?

481
00:27:25,400 --> 00:27:26,130
Your parents

482
00:27:26,310 --> 00:27:27,640
travel often for work, right?

483
00:27:27,640 --> 00:27:28,830
In the next couple of days,

484
00:27:28,830 --> 00:27:30,030
I'll pay them a visit.

485
00:27:30,590 --> 00:27:31,200
Let's talk

486
00:27:31,920 --> 00:27:33,780
about this properly face to face.

487
00:27:34,720 --> 00:27:35,380
Come. Come.

488
00:27:36,880 --> 00:27:37,480
What is it?

489
00:27:38,030 --> 00:27:39,630
I'm here to hand in homework.

490
00:27:39,640 --> 00:27:41,300
Okay, okay, just give it to me.

491
00:27:41,810 --> 00:27:43,390
[Pre-filled College Application
Preference Form]

492
00:27:42,160 --> 00:27:43,560
Alright, you can go back.

493
00:27:43,790 --> 00:27:44,590
What's wrong?

494
00:27:48,830 --> 00:27:50,640
I'm worried that you might

495
00:27:51,200 --> 00:27:52,330
pick the wrong major

496
00:27:52,480 --> 00:27:54,160
and end up at a not-so-good university.

497
00:27:54,160 --> 00:27:54,640
With your grades...

498
00:27:54,640 --> 00:27:55,310
It's about time.

499
00:27:55,310 --> 00:27:55,920
Class is about to start.

500
00:27:55,920 --> 00:27:56,830
I'm heading off.

501
00:27:56,830 --> 00:27:57,490
Okay. Okay.

502
00:27:58,070 --> 00:27:59,730
Remember to call your father!

503
00:28:18,640 --> 00:28:19,700
What are you doing?

504
00:28:23,880 --> 00:28:25,880
You really didn't
fill out your application form?

505
00:28:25,880 --> 00:28:27,810
Do you want to discuss it together?

506
00:28:28,110 --> 00:28:28,570
No need.

507
00:28:29,200 --> 00:28:29,680
No need?

508
00:28:30,640 --> 00:28:31,200
Really?

509
00:28:33,160 --> 00:28:34,070
Really?

510
00:28:35,200 --> 00:28:35,790
No need.

511
00:28:36,920 --> 00:28:37,350
Oh.

512
00:28:37,880 --> 00:28:38,480
Okay then.

513
00:28:39,880 --> 00:28:40,740
Suit yourself.

514
00:28:43,680 --> 00:28:44,880
Just remember,

515
00:28:45,590 --> 00:28:47,120
I'll always be on your side.

516
00:28:48,160 --> 00:28:49,360
If there's anything,

517
00:28:49,400 --> 00:28:50,460
come to me anytime.

518
00:28:56,640 --> 00:28:57,900
What's with that look?

519
00:29:10,760 --> 00:29:14,370
♪ The story begins with hand in hand ♪

520
00:29:15,440 --> 00:29:17,460
♪ For no reason at all ♪

521
00:29:17,620 --> 00:29:20,470
♪ I just want to walk with you ♪

522
00:29:21,300 --> 00:29:25,800
♪ Simply until we grow old ♪

523
00:29:26,510 --> 00:29:30,330
♪ Every warm touch that drew us closer ♪

524
00:29:30,900 --> 00:29:32,810
♪ Was nothing but a dream ♪

525
00:29:33,380 --> 00:29:36,820
♪ So many sunrises and sunsets ♪

526
00:29:37,120 --> 00:29:40,850
♪ Have changed our original hearts ♪

527
00:29:41,530 --> 00:29:45,030
♪ By not thinking about it or guessing ♪

528
00:29:45,220 --> 00:29:48,340
♪ I thought I could break free ♪

529
00:29:48,580 --> 00:29:55,500
♪ Time has shown
I'm not as carefree as I imagined ♪

530
00:29:54,720 --> 00:29:55,400
I'm going to be late!

531
00:29:55,400 --> 00:29:56,860
I'm leaving! I'm leaving!

532
00:29:57,020 --> 00:30:01,180
♪ I still can't forget the tenderness
you gave me that year ♪

533
00:30:01,270 --> 00:30:04,860
♪ Exhausting all my strength,
I still can't fool myself ♪

534
00:30:02,960 --> 00:30:04,490
He didn't wait for me again.

535
00:30:04,950 --> 00:30:08,300
♪ Your place is still here ♪

536
00:30:08,400 --> 00:30:12,780
♪ No one else can take it ♪

537
00:30:12,720 --> 00:30:13,830
Sorry, Sir.

538
00:30:12,840 --> 00:30:16,730
♪ Let me treat it as just a heavy rain ♪

539
00:30:14,110 --> 00:30:15,310
Hurry up and sit down.

540
00:30:16,790 --> 00:30:21,460
♪ Gradually, the memories we've built
become clear ♪

541
00:30:21,590 --> 00:30:26,250
♪ All composed into a song ♪

542
00:30:23,920 --> 00:30:25,120
Where is Tong Xiaole?

543
00:30:25,440 --> 00:30:26,440
He hasn't come yet.

544
00:30:26,440 --> 00:30:27,200
He hasn't come yet?

545
00:30:27,200 --> 00:30:30,460
♪ It's still so beautiful ♪

546
00:30:29,550 --> 00:30:30,750
Where is Tong Xiaole?

547
00:30:33,400 --> 00:30:34,830
I thought he had already come.
